  "notes": "Algerian Arabic. Complex dialect landscape from Oran (west) to Constantine (east). Intermediate between Moroccan (more reduced) and Tunisian. θ → /t/ or /s/; ð → /d/ or /z/. ق → /q/ (eastern) or /ɡ/ (western, Oran area). Berber substrate (especially Kabylie) reinforces emphatics. French integration deepest of all Maghrebi dialects (130+ years colonial rule).",
